Latest news of algae blossoms: Condensation decreases in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest news from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general decrease in algae bloom concentrations in parts of the Tampa Bay region.
According to the FWC, wearier algae blooms are reported in certain areas in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota Charlotte and Collier counties - suggesting decreasing concentrations.
The algae flower covers about 200 kilometres of coastline from the northern part of Pinellas to the southern part of the Lee counties.
You can find unique flowers about 16 miles from Hillsborough County, but in fewer places compared to last week.
Algae blooms have also been reported in Pasco County.
Moderate concentrations in or near Pinellas County were reported last week, low to high off-shore concentrations in Hillsborough County, very low to high concentrations in Manatee County, very low to high concentrations in or near Sarasota County, very low to medium concentrations in Charlotte County, and low concentrations in Sarasota County.
Respiratory irritation is still reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier counties.
No respiratory irritation was reported in northwestern Florida during the past week.
